# VoiceBlender Docker access-control rules — iptables-save / iptables-restore format.
#
# Loaded into the VB-FILTER chain (hung off Docker's DOCKER-USER chain) by
# firewall/vb-firewall.sh. Edit the "allowed sources" lines below to manage the
# allowlist, then re-run:  sudo firewall/vb-firewall.sh apply
#
# Notes:
#   * __EXT_IF__ is a placeholder; vb-firewall.sh substitutes the host's external
#     interface (auto-detected, or VB_EXT_IF / --iface). Inter-container traffic
#     arrives on the docker bridge, not __EXT_IF__, so it is never matched.
#   * Ports are matched container-side (post-DNAT): REST+VSI tcp/8080, SIP udp/5060,
#     SIP-TLS tcp/5061. Cluster host ports 8081/8082 DNAT to 8080 and are covered.
#   * RTP/media (udp 10000-20000) and MoQ (udp 8443) are intentionally NOT listed,
#     so they stay open.
#   * Host-local access (localhost) traverses OUTPUT, not FORWARD, so it is unaffected.
#
# Allowlist entries accept a single IP or a CIDR, e.g.:
#   -A VB-FILTER -i __EXT_IF__ -p tcp --dport 8080 -s 198.51.100.0/24 -j RETURN

*filter
:VB-FILTER - [0:0]

# ---- allowed sources (EDIT THESE) ----------------------------------------
# REST API + VSI WebSocket (tcp/8080)
-A VB-FILTER -i __EXT_IF__ -p tcp --dport 8080 -s 203.0.113.10 -j RETURN
# SIP signalling (udp/5060)
-A VB-FILTER -i __EXT_IF__ -p udp --dport 5060 -s 203.0.113.10 -j RETURN
# SIP over TLS (tcp/5061)
-A VB-FILTER -i __EXT_IF__ -p tcp --dport 5061 -s 203.0.113.10 -j RETURN

# ---- default deny for protected ports (keep at the end) -------------------
-A VB-FILTER -i __EXT_IF__ -p tcp --dport 8080 -j DROP
-A VB-FILTER -i __EXT_IF__ -p udp --dport 5060 -j DROP
-A VB-FILTER -i __EXT_IF__ -p tcp --dport 5061 -j DROP
COMMIT
